{"article_id":"svP2lsp8JMbb08BA","edus":[{"id":0,"text":"Sen. Cindy Hyde-Smith","depth":6},{"id":1,"text":"( R-MI )","depth":6},{"id":2,"text":"won her runoff election last night over Democrat Mike Espy in Mississippi ,","depth":5},{"id":3,"text":"so Republicans have a solid 53-47 majority .","depth":4},{"id":4,"text":"No longer will we have to deal with the Murkowski-Collins question","depth":4},{"id":5,"text":"when it come sot tight votes of judicial and Supreme Court nominations .","depth":4},{"id":6,"text":"We can run the table on paper ,","depth":4},{"id":7,"text":"but we have a Sen. Jeff Flake","depth":8},{"id":8,"text":"( R-AZ )","depth":8},{"id":9,"text":"problem .","depth":7},{"id":10,"text":"Yeah , Mr. Flake , the perpetual pain in the rear end of the Senate GOP , isn ' t budging from his position","depth":10},{"id":11,"text":"of blocking Trump ' s judicial nominees","depth":10},{"id":12,"text":"until a vote on a bill","depth":11},{"id":13,"text":"to protect Special Counsel Robert Mueller and the Russia investigation","depth":11},{"id":14,"text":"is brought before the Senate floor .","depth":10},{"id":15,"text":"His antics caused the Senate Judiciary Committee to cancel tomorrow ' s hearing","depth":11},{"id":16,"text":"to advance 21 judicial nominees .","depth":11},{"id":17,"text":"Flake is the deciding vote on that committee ,","depth":11},{"id":18,"text":"and he ' s starting to annoy the hell out of his Republican colleagues .","depth":11},{"id":19,"text":"Efforts to appease him","depth":12},{"id":20,"text":"seem to be a fool ' s errand","depth":12},{"id":21,"text":"as binding legislation","depth":14},{"id":22,"text":"to protect Mueller","depth":14},{"id":23,"text":"is the only thing","depth":14},{"id":24,"text":"that will cause him to reverse course on his obstructionism over judicial nominees","depth":14},{"id":25,"text":"( via Politico ) :","depth":12},{"id":26,"text":"The Senate Judiciary Committee cancelled a Thursday hearing on judicial nominees","depth":11},{"id":27,"text":"as Jeff Flake ' s stand for a bill","depth":13},{"id":28,"text":"to protect special counsel Robert Mueller","depth":13},{"id":29,"text":"continues to wreak havoc in the lame duck session .","depth":12},{"id":30,"text":"The panel was scheduled to advance six Circuit Court nominees , 15 District Court nominees and several bipartisan bills on Thursday","depth":10},{"id":31,"text":"to prepare them for possible floor action over the next month .","depth":10},{"id":32,"text":"But Flake ,","depth":11},{"id":33,"text":"who is retiring at the end of this year ,","depth":11},{"id":34,"text":"is holding firm to his vow","depth":11},{"id":35,"text":"to vote against judicial nominees on the floor and in committee","depth":12},{"id":36,"text":"unless Senate Majority Leader Mitch McConnell","depth":14},{"id":37,"text":"( R-Ky. )","depth":14},{"id":38,"text":"schedules a vote on the bipartisan special counsel legislation .","depth":13},{"id":39,"text":"Flake and Sen. Chris Coons","depth":12},{"id":40,"text":"( D-Del . )","depth":12},{"id":41,"text":"attempted to bring up the bill on Wednesday","depth":11},{"id":42,"text":"and were blocked by Republicans","depth":11},{"id":43,"text":"that oppose it .","depth":11},{"id":44,"text":"Relatedly , Flake voted against Thomas Farr ' s nomination","depth":12},{"id":45,"text":"to be a District Court judge","depth":12},{"id":46,"text":"on Wednesday afternoon ,","depth":11},{"id":47,"text":"forcing Vice President Mike Pence to break a tie","depth":11},{"id":48,"text":"after wavering Sen. Tim Scott","depth":13},{"id":49,"text":"( R-S.C. )","depth":13},{"id":50,"text":"voted to advance Farr .","depth":12},{"id":51,"text":"Flake ' s blockade is annoying senior Republicans","depth":7},{"id":52,"text":"by slowing down confirmation of conservative judges in the narrowly divided Senate .","depth":7},{"id":53,"text":"But Flake ' s tactics have been effective","depth":7},{"id":54,"text":"because Republicans have a one-seat majority on the Judiciary Committee","depth":9},{"id":55,"text":"and control just 51 votes in the Senate ,","depth":9},{"id":56,"text":"so he could have tagged some nominees with an \" unfavorable \" recommendation","depth":9},{"id":57,"text":"if Democrats unanimously opposed them .","depth":9},{"id":58,"text":"For those","depth":9},{"id":59,"text":"who think","depth":10},{"id":60,"text":"Jeff Flake would have won in Arizona ,","depth":10},{"id":61,"text":"let me remind you","depth":9},{"id":62,"text":"that his popularity in is state is straight trash ,","depth":9},{"id":63,"text":"he barely won his 2012 race ,","depth":7},{"id":64,"text":"and he most likely would have been picked off in a primary .","depth":6},{"id":65,"text":"Jeff Flake can not leave the Senate soon enough .","depth":5},{"id":66,"text":"Oh , and Flake and the late John McCain ' s squishy antics seemed to have depressed Arizona GOP enthusiasm ,","depth":7},{"id":67,"text":"so there ' s that aspect .","depth":7},{"id":68,"text":"If Flake wants to run in 2020 ,","depth":8},{"id":69,"text":"and there ' s some speculation","depth":9},{"id":70,"text":"that he ' s considering it ,","depth":9},{"id":71,"text":"he better be prepared to be ripped apart by angry conservatives","depth":8},{"id":72,"text":"for going out of his way","depth":9},{"id":73,"text":"to torpedo the Republican agenda on the Hill","depth":10},{"id":74,"text":"to spite Trump .","depth":10},{"id":75,"text":"Oh , and expect to be speaking to just a handful of people","depth":8},{"id":76,"text":"who show up at his low energy rallies .","depth":8},{"id":77,"text":"Get lost , dude .","depth":7},{"id":78,"text":"Flake is causing problems now for GOP","depth":7},{"id":79,"text":"and is not buckling .","depth":7},{"id":80,"text":"Hearing on 21 lifetime noms","depth":4},{"id":81,"text":"cancelled over his judicial blockade","depth":4},{"id":82,"text":"https : //t.co/9gaYu4eBlB","depth":3},{"id":83,"text":"- Burgess Everett","depth":4},{"id":84,"text":"( @ burgessev )","depth":4},{"id":85,"text":"November 28 , 2018","depth":3}],"relations":[{"parent":171,"left":165,"right":170,"relation":"context","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":165,"left":91,"right":164,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":91,"left":89,"right":90,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":89,"left":88,"right":3,"relation":"causal","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":88,"left":87,"right":2,"relation":"same-unit","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":87,"left":0,"right":1,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":90,"left":4,"right":5,"relation":"context","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":164,"left":142,"right":163,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":142,"left":6,"right":141,"relation":"adversative","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":141,"left":134,"right":140,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":134,"left":93,"right":133,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":93,"left":92,"right":9,"relation":"same-unit","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":92,"left":7,"right":8,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":133,"left":112,"right":132,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":112,"left":97,"right":111,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":97,"left":94,"right":96,"relation":"context","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":94,"left":10,"right":11,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":96,"left":95,"right":14,"relation":"same-unit","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":95,"left":12,"right":13,"relation":"purpose","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":111,"left":100,"right":110,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":100,"left":98,"right":99,"relation":"context","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":98,"left":15,"right":16,"relation":"purpose","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":99,"left":17,"right":18,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":110,"left":106,"right":109,"relation":"explanation","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":106,"left":101,"right":105,"relation":"explanation","nuclea